## 2) Root `CONTRIBUTING.md` 

```md
# Contributing

Thank you for contributing to this project.

## Mandatory Language Rule

This repository is **English-only** for:
- documentation
- code comments
- commit messages
- pull requests
- issues

---

## Branch Strategy

- `main` = stable branch
- Feature branches:
  - `feat/<short-description>`
  - `fix/<short-description>`
  - `refactor/<short-description>`
  - `docs/<short-description>`

Examples:
- `feat/add-watchparty-validation`
- `fix/login-lockout-race-condition`

---

## Commit Message Format

Use Conventional Commits:

- `feat:`
- `fix:`
- `refactor:`
- `docs:`
- `test:`
- `chore:`

Examples:
- `feat(auth): add OTP verification endpoint`
- `fix(api): return 400 on invalid watchparty payload`
- `docs(readme): add monorepo setup instructions`

---

## Pull Request Checklist

Before opening a PR:

- [ ] Title and description are in English
- [ ] Scope is focused and small
- [ ] No secrets are committed
- [ ] Relevant tests were run locally
- [ ] Behavior changes are documented
- [ ] Breaking changes are clearly labeled

---

## Code Quality Guidelines

- Keep controllers thin; move logic into services
- Validate request input (`@Valid`, DTOs)
- Prefer explicit error handling over catch-all blocks
- Avoid manual JSON string construction
- Add/update tests when changing logic

---

## Security Rules

- Never commit real API keys, passwords, or tokens
- Use environment variables and secret managers
- If a secret is leaked, rotate immediately
- Review dependency updates regularly

---

## Reporting Issues

Please include:
- expected behavior
- actual behavior
- steps to reproduce
- logs/screenshots (if relevant)